{
  "texts": [
    "This isn't to say, of course, that the reasons they would give us would necessarily be good.",
    "But when they fail to give us good reason, we could reject their recommendations on those grounds.",
    "by platforms, they would shift power toward users.",
    "They would most plausibly be funded through subscription and could be integrated into operating systems, which have less incentive to maximize our engagement or to allocate our attention to any particular platform or type of content.",
    "Without such problematic incentives, generative agents could then prioritize facilitating our judicious attention allocation, responding directly to our stated moral values and thereby augmenting our attentional moral skill."
  ]
}